summary:
Peter: How does Mj know I’m Spider-Man?
Ned: Well too be honest, you make it too easy for everyone to assume you’re Spider-Man....
body:
Peter: How does Mj know I’m Spider-Man?

Ned: Well too be honest, you make it too easy for everyone to assume you’re Spider-Man.

Peter: I think I’m very good at keeping secrets.

*Thinks back to crawling on the ceiling with Ned in the bedroom, leaves the door open where Aunt May sees Peter changing into his suit, Tony Stark easily finding his identity and finding where he hides his suit. Leaves the school bus to follow a giant donut space ship, not aware that Mj could possibly be hanging in the front, noticing him jumping out and hanging against the side of the bus where cars are driving in the background, seeing some teenage kid stuck to the side of the bus, with a red mask and hurling over the bridge*

Peter: I’m very sure that I’m good at keep secrets.

title: It's been a long, long time.
body:

by Sasshask

*ENDGAME SPOILERS*
°
°
°
°
°
°

Steve estaba herido, pensó en la vida después de Tony y sabia que podría ser feliz pero no tan feliz como lo habría hecho si hubiera vivido esa vida con Tony.

Había perdido la oportunidad o eso creía hasta que estuvo sobre esa plataforma con las gemas en su mano.

Podía tener otra oportunidad sin afectar lo que suceda, si funcionaba no volvería a dejar pasar su oportunidad.
